# Communis — Shared Substrate

> *Latin*: **communis** — "common / shared / belonging to all".
> Not a utility dump: the deliberate substrate of primitives every
> subsystem needs but no subsystem owns.

## Philosophical Role

Communis is the arena of facts nobody disputes. Time, logs, config,
JSON escaping, ring buffers, Tegra sysfs probes — these are not the
charter of Conscientia, Machina, or Memoria. They precede them. Every
subsystem includes from here; nothing here includes from anywhere else.

This is the **only** place where naming must be English-pragmatic rather
than Latin-philosophical: a timestamp is a timestamp, a ring buffer is
a ring buffer. Inventing Latin cloaks for library primitives would be
tech-dynamics dressed as philosophy.

## Invariants

- **Zero inbound dependency on subsystems.** If `communis/foo.h` needs
  to `#include "machina/bar.h"`, the abstraction is wrong — the shared
  thing is not shared, it is a Machina thing in disguise.
- **Header-only where reasonable** (`json_util.h`, `ring_buffer.h`,
  `log.h`) so that dependents pay only for what they touch.
- **`tempus` lives here** (three-tier clock T0/T1/T2 — see architecture
  RFC 09), because time is the most common of all shared facts.

## Contract with Surrounding Subsystems

- Every subsystem `#include`s at least one header from Communis.
- Communis never `#include`s from `conscientia/`, `machina/`,
  `memoria/`, `nexus/`, `orator/`, `sensus/`, `actus/`.
- New helpers join Communis only after a second caller appears.
  A single-caller helper belongs inside that caller's subsystem.

## Current State

`config.{cpp,h}`, `log.h`, `json_util.h`, `ring_buffer.h`,
`tegra.{cpp,h}`, `tegra_throttle.{cpp,h}`, `timeline_logger.{cpp,h}`,
`thread_naming.h`. All within R1.
